- **Application**: The segmentation of the market by application into fruits & vegetables, cereals & grains, oilseeds & pulses, and others highlights the versatility of biofungicides in addressing a wide array of crop types. Different biofungicides may be employed based on the unique requirements of each crop category, ensuring targeted and efficient disease management strategies.

- **Formulation**: The segmentation of biofungicides for soil treatment by formulation into liquid and dry options serves the practical needs of farmers in terms of application and storage. Liquid formulations are user-friendly, easy to apply, and mix, while dry formulations boast longer shelf lives and enhanced convenience for storage and transportation, catering to varied preferences in agricultural practices.

- **Mode of Action**: The classification of biofungicides based on mode of action into competition, antibiosis, mycoparasitism, and induced resistance provides a comprehensive overview of how these products target fungal pathogens. Each mode of action offers distinct mechanisms for controlling soil-borne diseases, empowering farmers with a diverse toolkit to combat fungal infections effectively.

